<p>
  <span class="nym">Pelagius</span>
  <span class="gen">m.</span>
  
  <span class="etym">A derivative of <span class="lang">Ancient Greek</span> <i>πέλαγος</i> 'sea'.
  </span>
  
</p>
  
<div class="usg">
  <p>The name of a 3rd C Croatian martyr, a 4th-5th C British moralist whose views were condemned as heretical in the early 5th C, two 6th C popes, an 8th C king of Asturias, and a 10th C Spanish saint.</p>
</div>
  
  
<div class="def">
  <p>The name was most common in the Iberian peninsula.</p>
  
  


